  Bureau of Land Management is offering free food and housing to volunteers to live in Garnet Ghost Town and work as a tour operator . 
  The Montana mining town was abandoned after a fire in 1912 . 
  It was established in the 1860s by miners looking for gold and silver . 
  Garnet was devastated by fire and abandoned in 1912 but is now set to become a tourist stop . 
 